this nearly 14-foot-tall statue was carved more than 130 years ago in Cuba for Vicente Martinez Ybor. Originally commissioned as a grand marketing statement, she boldly proclaimed to the world that the finest cigars were being made in Tampa, Florida.\u2060\n\u2060\nQueen Isabella traveled the globe as the centerpiece of Ybor\u2019s cigar exhibitions, showcased at world fairs in Paris, London, and Chicago\u2014offering a majestic glimpse into Tampa\u2019s booming cigar industry and the vibrant immigrant community that helped build it.\u2060\n\u2060\nShe ultimately returned to Ybor City, where she stood proudly in Ybor\u2019s cigar factory\u2014until time took its toll. For decades, she sat in disrepair, a forgotten monarch of a bygone era. Espa\u00f1ol.\u2060\n\u2060\nQueen Isabella once again steps into the light, returning to her Spanish roots and to a home that honors the very history she embodies.\u2060\n\u2060\nWe are proud to
